A tangle of blackberry canes spilled over the top of a garden fence, dotted with fat dark berries. Vix, shouting until her voice cracked, circled below and at last reared up on her hind legs. The crown of her head reached 4 feet from the trampled grass, and a strong push of the haunches added another 2 feet to the upward bound. The juice-stained leaves trembled. She eyed the darkest berry and gathered herself for the spring.

Question: the highest point Vix can reach with a single leap?
