Strength shared is strength multiplied — a truth the Lion knew well, and worked patiently to undo. All this took place near the forest.

In the valley grassland by the slow stream, where 8 bulls had once drunk together at the same bend, only a few survivors now picked their way between the reeds. Roar the lion had taken 7 of the herd already over many quiet weeks, and the bulls left alive in a panic would not even stand near each other to drink. From a willow shadow, the lion watched with eyes always on the path. He began to count, on the soft pads of his paws, how many bulls of the original number remained.

Question: how many bulls remain?
<|end|>
