Whisk the country mouse opened her little leather pouch by the hearth of a hollow stump, content in her quiet life: inside lay 21 cheese rinds saved from a farmer's table. Far away, in a wallpapered drawer behind a townhouse skirting board, Nibble the city mouse counted 25 cake crumbs swept from a kitchen tray, with a hungry gleam in his eye. Each mouse looked at the other's tally and wondered, in her own way, who had truly more.

Write a Clojure expression that computes the absolute difference between Whisk and Nibble's food counts.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
{"tool_calls":[{"name":"eval","args":{"form":"(let [country-amt 21 city-amt 25] (abs (- city-amt country-amt)))"}}]}
<|end|>


