Two creatures of the meadow approached the coming winter very differently.

In the long blue hour after noon, with snow piled to the rafters, Tic sat by a small lamp and went over the inventory once again. The basket that held the winter's food contained exactly 89 grains. He measured out 3 grains as a single day's portion — that was the rule he had set for himself when summer was bright. Now he only had to work out how many days the supply would carry him.

Question: how many whole days Tic's stockpile will last?
