Nibble the mouse buttoned a small embroidered purse holding 72 coins into a hidden inner pocket, imagining all that he might gain at the thought of a festival in the city. The carriage fare came to 22 coins, paid reluctantly to a tall driver who bowed to no one. At a market stall, Nibble parted with another 22 coins for a wedge of cheese and a slice of plum cake. The purse, once heavy, was much thinner now.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many coins Nibble has left after the trip.
<|end|>
