At the meadow, the days began with Bit setting out before the sun and ended with them hauling another load of crumbs into the pouch hidden under the roots. The Grasshopper watched lazily from a stalk of grass, certain summer would last forever. But Bit kept a quieter count: Bit worked the whole 71 days of summer and finished with 213 crumbs stored away. The pouch grew fuller by the day.

