What the Dog thought he saw beneath the water turned out to be his own reflection.

Bell the dog had been allowed exactly 4 bread chunks from the morning loaf by the baker's wife, who had arranged them carefully on a low plank for her to carry home. On the brook crossing the water mirrored her, and his thoughts already on more, she lunged at the seeming rival's mouthful. One soft chunk fell into the brook and dissolved at once. She reached the doorstep, regretting every careless step, and the loaf-keeper saw plainly the gap between the careful count and the count that actually arrived.

