Bell the dog trotted across a low stone footbridge with 6 bones clamped firmly between her jaws, feeling very pleased with the morning's prize. Halfway over, she glanced down at the slow brown water and saw — imagining all that he might gain — what looked like another dog below, with the very same load. She opened her mouth to snatch at that other dog's bone, but of course the moment her jaws parted a single bone tumbled away into the stream and was gone. She stood blinking, his heart sinking.

