Clara balanced her wooden pail on her head and walked the road to market with 21 cups of fresh milk swaying gently above her. His eyes greedy with want, she was halfway through her daydream when her foot caught a stone and the pail tipped. 3 cups splashed down into the dust. Each of those cups would have sold for 1 coin at the stalls. His heart sinking, she stared at the pale pool darkening the road.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many coins Clara lost by spilling.
<|end|>
