All summer long, the Ant worked while the Grasshopper sang.

A storm rolled across the garden one afternoon, and the Grasshopper darted under a leaf to wait it out. Toc, however, only paused long enough to shake the rain from her back before trundling another biscuit into the hole she kept beside the back wall of the burrow. The work did not stop for weather; by the close of summer Toc had gathered 130 biscuits in all, carrying 2 biscuits home each day.

Write a Clojure expression that computes how many days Toc spent at the gathering.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
{"tool_calls":[{"name":"eval","args":{"form":"(let [total 130 per-day 2] (quot total per-day))"}}]}
